sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Creates an address resource in the specified project by using the data included in the request.

Inputs:

  • Project ID - Unique ID of the project.
  • Name - Name of the resource.
  • IP Version - IP version that will be used by this address.
  • Description - Description of this resource.

Outputs:

  • Address - Address is on object containing Name, ID, Operation Type, Target Link, Target ID, Status, User, Progress, Insert Time, Start Time, Self-Link, Region, Kind.
  • Status - If the request is executed successfully, Status is set to “Success”. If there is a failure in Google Virtual Private Cloud, Status is set to “Error".
  • Error Message - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

Error Messages:

  • Invalid Project ID has been passed.
  • Invalid authorization header. The access token you're using is either expired or invalid.

To use this action, a corresponding Google Virtual Private Cloud connection and credential must be created and associated with the Google Virtual Private Cloud Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.
